article.headline: Colgate 55, Army 53
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. -- Alex Woodhouse blocked a game-tying shot with less than five seconds to play, and Colgate beat Army 55-53 in Patriot League basketball Saturday. Yaw Gyawu led the Raiders (8-14, 4-5) with 12 points, while Mike Venezia chipped in 10. Woodhouse scored nine points and grabbed a game-high eight rebounds. Army's Josh Miller led all scorers with 18 points in 31 minutes off the bench. Cleveland Richard added 12 points for the Black Knights (7-15, 3-5), all in the second half. After a 6 for 21 showing in the first half, the Black Knights shot 48.4 percent in the second half to finish at 40.4 percent for the game. The Raiders held a 29-28 advantage on the glass. The Black Knights trailed by 14 at halftime but outscored the Raiders 36-24 in the second half.
